rio Sesti || Italy\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''This Is The War Room!'' (Short) || data-sort-value=\"Hars\"| Boris Hars-Tschachotin || Germany\n|}\n:<span style=\"background:#FFDEAD\">Highlighted titles</span> indicate the Best Restored Film and Best Documentary on Cinema official awards respectively.<ref name=\"Venice\"/>\n\n===Biennale College - Cinema===\nThe following films were selected for the Biennale College - Cinema section.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/2017/biennale-cinema-2017-biennale-college-cinema |title=Biennale Cinema 2017, Biennale College Cinema |work=labiennale.org |accessdate=17 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:95%\"\n! Title\n! Director(s)\n! Production Country\n|-\n| ''Beautiful Things'' || Giorgio Ferrero || Italy\n|-\n| ''Martyr'' || Mazen Khaled || Lebanon\n|-\n| ''Strange Colours'' || Alena Lodkina || Australia\n|}\n\n===Il Cinema nel Giardino===\nThe following films were selected for the ''Il Cinema nel Giardino'' section:<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/07/venice-film-festival-2017-lineup-full-list-1202137114/|title=Venice Film Festival Sets Lido Launch For Aronofsky, Clooney, Del Toro, Payne & More As Awards Buzz Begins \u2013 Full List|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=27 July 2017|accessdate=7 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" width=\"95%\"\n|-\n! English title\n! Original title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-\n| {{N/A}} || ''Controfigura'' || R\u00e4 di Martino || Italy, France, Switzerland, Morocco\n|-\n| {{N/A}} || ''Manuel'' || Dario Albertini || Italy\n|-\n| {{N/A}} || ''Nato a Casal di Principe'' || Bruno Oliviero || Italy, Spain\n|-\n| {{N/A}} || ''Suburra - La serie'' || [[Michele Placido]], [[Andrea Molaioli]], [[Giuseppe Capotondi]] || Italy\n|-\n| ''[[Above the Law (2017 film)|Above the Law]]'' || ''Tueurs'' || Fran\u00e7ois Troukens, Jean-Fran\u00e7ois Hensgens || Belgium, France\n|-\n|  colspan=2| ''[[Woodshock]]'' || [[Rodarte|Kate Mulleavy]], [[Rodarte|Laura Mulleavy]] || United States\n|}\n\n===Special screenings===\nThe following films were presented as Special screening of the Official Selection:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/2017/biennale-cinema-2017-proiezioni-speciali |title=Biennale Cinema 2017, Special screenings |work=labiennale.org |accessdate=18 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" width=\"95%\"\n|-\n! English title\n! Original title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-\n| {{N/A}} || ''Barbiana '65: La lezione di Don Milani'' || data-sort-value=\"D\u2019Alessandro\"| Alessandro G.A. D\u2019Alessandro || Italy\n|-\n| colspan=2 data-sort-value=\"Electric\"| ''[[The Electric Horseman]]'' (1979) || data-sort-value=\"Pollack\"| [[Sydney Pollack]] || United States\n|-\n| {{N/A}} || ''Lievito madre: Le ragazze del secolo scorso'' || data-sort-value=\"De Gregorio\"| Concita De Gregorio, Esmeralda Calabria || Italy\n|-\n| {{N/A}} || ''La lunga strada del ritorno'' (1962) || data-sort-value=\"Blasetti\"| [[Alessandro Blasetti]] || Italy\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Order\"| ''The Order of Things'' || ''L\u2019ordine delle cose'' || data-sort-value=\"Segre\"| [[Andrea Segre]] || Italy, France\n|}\n\n==Autonomous sections==\n===International Critics' Week===\nThe following films were selected for the 32nd Venice International Critics' Week:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sicvenezia.it/edizione/32-settimana-internazionale-della-critica/?lang=en |title=32nd International Film Critics\u2019 Week |work=sicvenezia.it |accessdate=18 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sicvenezia.it/4178/edizione-2017/notizie-2017/sic-at-sic-short-italian-cinema-2017/?lang=en |title=SIC@SIC 2017 Short Italian Cinema @ Settimana Internazionale della Critica |work=sicvenezia.it |accessdate=15 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/festivals/venice-critics-week-announced-opener-is-britains-pin-cushion-1202504174/|title=Venice Critics' Week Lineup Announced; Opener Is Britain's ''Pin Cushion''|accessdate=27 July 2017|work=Variety}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:0px\"\n! colspan=4| In competition\n|-\n! English title\n! Original title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-\n| ''Crater'' || data-sort-value=\"Cratere\"| ''Il Cratere'' || data-sort-value=\"Bellino\"| Luca Bellino, Silvia Luzi || Italy\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[Drift (2017 film)|Drift]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Wittmann\"| Helena Wittmann || Germany\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Gulf\"| ''The Gulf'' || ''K\u00f6rfez'' || data-sort-value=\"Yeksan\"| Emre Yeksan || Turkey, Germany, Greece\n|-\n| ''[[Hunting Season (2017 film)|Hunting Season]]'' || ''Temporada de caza'' || data-sort-value=\"Garagiola\"| Natalia Garagiola || Argentina, United States, Germany, France, Qatar\n|-\n| ''Sarah Plays a Werewolf'' || ''Sarah joue un loup garou'' || data-sort-value=\"Wyss\"| Katharina Wyss || Switzerland, Germany\n|-\n| ''Team Hurricane'' || ''Team Hurricane'' || data-sort-value=\"Berg\"| Annika Berg || Denmark\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Wild\"| ''[[The Wild Boys (film)|The Wild Boys]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Garcons\"| ''Les gar\u00e7ons sauvages'' || data-sort-value=\"Mandico\"| Bertrand Mandico || France\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:0px\"\n! colspan=4| Special Events - Out of competition\n|-\n! Line-up\n! Title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-\n| Opening film || ''[[Pin Cushion (film)|Pin Cushion]]'' || Deborah Haywood || United Kingdom\n|-\n| Closing film || {{ill|Poison (2017 film)|lt=''Poison''|it|Veleno (film 2017)}} (''Veleno'') || Diego Olivares || Italy\n|}\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:0px\"\n! colspan=4| SIC@SIC 2017 <small>(Short Italian Cinema @ Settimana Internazionale della Critica)</small>\n|-\n! Italian title\n! English title\n! width=\"5%\"| Min.\n! Director(s)\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''Adavede'' || 20' || Alain Parroni\n|-\n| ''Due'' || ''Two'' || 17' || Riccardo Giacconi\n|-\n| ''Les fant\u00f4mes de la veille'' || ''Ghosts of Yesterday'' || 20' || Manuel Billi\n|-\n| ''Il legionario'' || ''The Legionnaire'' || 13' || Hleb Papou\n|-\n| ''MalaM\u00e8nti'' || ''MeanMinds'' || 13' || Francesco Di Leva\n|-\n| ''Piccole italiane'' || ''Little Italian Girls'' || 18' || Letizia Lamartire\n|-\n| ''Le visite'' || ''Visiting Day'' || 15' || Elio Di Pace\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:0px\"\n! colspan=5| Special Events\n|-\n! Line-up\n! Italian title\n! English title\n! width=\"5%\"| Min.\n! Director(s)\n|-\n| Opening Short Film || ''Nausicaa L'altra odissea'' || ''Nausicaa - The Other Odyssey'' || 20' || Bepi Vigna\n|-\n| Closing Short Film || ''L\u2019ultimo miracolo' || ''The Last Miracle'' || 20' || Enrico Pau\n|}\n\n===Venice Days===\nThe following films were selected for the 14th edition of the Venice Days (Giornate degli Autori) section:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.venice-days.com/2017/film.asp?lang=eng |title=Venice Days, 14th edition, Films |work=venice-days.com |accessdate=17 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/festivals/venice-days-chloe-sevigny-kim-nguyen-pengfei-1202505558/|title=Venice Days: Works by Chloe Sevigny, Canada\u2019s Kim Nguyen, China\u2019s Pengfei in Lineup|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=25 July 2016|accessdate=24 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:0px\"\n! colspan=4| Official selection\n|-\n! English title\n! Original title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-style=\"background:#FFDEAD\"\n| colspan=2| ''[[Candelaria (film)|Candelaria]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Hinestroza\"| [[Jhonny Hendrix Hinestroza]] || Colombia, Germany, Norway, Argentina, Cuba\n|-\n| ''[[Equilibrium (2017 film)|Equilibrium]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Equilibrio\"| ''L'equilibrio'' || data-sort-value=\"Marra\"| [[Vincenzo Marra]] || Italy\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[Eye on Juliet]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Nguyen\"| [[Kim Nguyen]] || Canada\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[Life Guidance]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Mader\"| [[Ruth Mader]] || Austria\n|-\n| ''[[Longing (2017 film)|Longing]]'' || ''Ga'agua'' || data-sort-value=\"Gabizon\"| [[Savi Gabizon]] || Israel\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[Looking for Oum Kulthum]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Neshat\"| [[Shirin Neshat]] || Germany, Austria, Italy, Lebanon, Qatar\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[M (2017 film)|M]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Forestier\"| [[Sara Forestier]] || France\n|-\n| ''[[Samui Song]]'' ||  || data-sort-value=\"Ratanaruang\"| [[Pen-ek Ratanaruang]] || Thailand, Germany, Norway\n|-\n| ''[[Tainted Souls]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Contagio\"| ''Il contagio'' || data-sort-value=\"Botrugno\"| [[Matteo Botrugno]], [[Daniele Coluccini]] || Italy\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Taste\"| ''[[The Taste of Rice Flower]]'' || ''Mi Hua Zhi Wei'' ( \u7c73\u82b1\u4e4b\u5473 ) || [[Pengfei]] || China\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[Volubilis (film)|Volubilis]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Bensa\u00efdi\"| [[Faouzi Bensa\u00efdi]] || Morocco, France, Qatar\n|-\n| ''[[Where the Shadows Fall]]'' || ''Dove cadono le ombre'' || data-sort-value=\"Pedicini\"| [[Valentina Pedicini]] || Italy\n|}  \n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:0px\"\n! colspan=4| Special events\n|-\n! English title\n! Original title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''Agnelli'' || Nick Hooker || United States\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''Getting Naked: A Burlesque Story'' || James Lester || United States\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ececec; font-size:smaller; text-align:center\" data-sort-value=\"Legge\"| N/A || data-sort-value=\"Legge\"| ''La legge del numero uno'' || [[Alessandro D'Alatri]] || Italy\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Resolute\"| ''The Resolute'' || data-sort-value=\"Risoluto\"| ''Il risoluto'' || Giovanni Donfrancesco || Italy, France\n|-\n| style=\"backgro